events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Detroit Pistons

headlines.description: — Jonas Valanciunas scored 13 of his 33 points in the first quarter and the New Orleans Pelicans went on to beat the Detroit Pistons 116-110 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Valanciunas scores 33 points, Pelicans beat Pistons 116-110

headlines.description: — John Collins tipped in a missed shot with less than a second left to give the Atlanta Hawks a 113-111 victory over the Indiana Pacers on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Collins beats buzzer with tip-in, Hawks edge Pacers 113-111

events.name: New York Knicks at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson scored 34 points, including a couple crucial free throws with 13.9 seconds left, and the New York Knicks held off a furious Washington rally in a 112-108 victory over the Wizards on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks hold off Wizards 112-108 despite Kuzma's 40

events.name: Golden State Warriors at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — In an environment they had never faced, the Golden State Warriors relied on their experience to make it feel like just another game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Warriors top Spurs 144-113 before NBA-record crowd of 68,323

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Chicago Bulls

headlines.description: — Josh Giddey matched a season high with 25 points and added 10 rebounds, helping the Oklahoma City Thunder to a 124-110 win over the Chicago Bulls on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Giddey scores 25, leads Thunder to 124-110 win over Bulls

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 31 points, D’Angelo Russell had 17 and the Minnesota Timberwolves held off the short-handed Phoenix Suns 121-116 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards, Timberwolves bounce back to beat short-handed Suns

headlines.description: — Lauri Markkanen scored 28 points and blocked Franz Wagner’s 3-pointer in the closing moments to power the Utah Jazz past the Orlando Magic, 112-108 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lauri Markkanen scores 28 points, Jazz beat Magic 112-108

headlines.description: — No Nikola Jokic, no problem for the Denver Nuggets. Especially when it comes to the Clippers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nuggets beat Clippers 115-103 for 5th straight win

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis had 19 points, a career-high 16 assists and 15 rebounds in his fourth triple-double of the season, and the Sacramento Kings beat the skidding Houston Rockets 139-114 on Friday night for their third straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis has triple-double, Kings rout skidding Rockets
